t deep body relaxation, start with <strong>Spoil Yourself Bath Salt <\/strong>or <strong>Epsom Salt<\/strong>. <br\/><\/li><li>If you want problem based options for sleep, stress, muscle, or head pressure, start with the <strong>Reset Kit<\/strong>. <br\/><\/li><li>If you want a daily inside habit, start with <strong>The Yellow Ritual <\/strong>(one tablet a day). <\/li><\/ul>","open_by_default":false,"use_custom_sizes":true,"q_size_desktop":20,"q_size_mobile":16,"a_size_desktop":14,"a_size_mobile":14}},"faq_HaXcV4":{"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"Should I take magnesium deficiency seriously?","answer":"<p><strong>Yes,<\/strong> but do not panic. If your body is constantly stressed, tired, tight, or not sleeping well, magnesium habits can matter. It is not about trends. It is about giving your nervous system and muscles better support.<\/p>","open_by_default":false,"use_custom_sizes":true,"q_size_desktop":20,"q_size_mobile":16,"a_size_desktop":14,"a_size_mobile":14}},"faq_MKeTTV":{"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"How do I know if magnesium support might help me?","answer":"<p>I cannot diagnose you, but I can share patterns people relate to. If you often feel tired but your mind does not slow down, or your body feels tight, restless, or heavy, magnesium rituals may help. Sometimes it shows up as poor sleep quality, stress build up, or sore muscles after a normal day.<\/p>","open_by_default":false,"use_custom_sizes":true,"q_size_desktop":20,"q_size_mobile":16,"a_size_desktop":14,"a_size_mobile":14}},"faq_ATRUDn":{"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"Should I choose salts or tablets?","answer":"<ul><li>Salts are for the body outside. They help you unwind through a soak. <br\/><\/li><li>Tablets are for inside support. They help you build a daily magnesium habit. <br\/><\/li><li>Many people use both, but you can start with one. <br\/><br\/>In View more, you will see the best starting point for your lifestyle.<\/li><\/ul>","open_by_default":false,"use_custom_siz